   "source": [
    "KPI Total Steps:\n",
    "It is the cumulative count of all recorded events (steps) triggered by a client (client_id) during a single visit (visit_id). \n",
    "    Every time a user interacts with a stage of the process—from the initial start to the final confirm—it is added to the count."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "02542b6d-ee4f-40a9-8fd1-4025c31e4e2a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Web Part 1: 4.56 steps \n",
      "Web Part 2: 4.98 steps\n",
      "Diference: 0.42  steps\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "df_demo = pd.read_csv('df_final_demo.csv') #demographic data\n",
    "web_pt1 = pd.read_csv('df_final_web_data_pt_1.txt') #web data 1\n",
    "web_pt2 = pd.read_csv('df_final_web_data_pt_2.txt') #web data for the test\n",
    "df_web_full = pd.concat([web_pt1, web_pt2]) #merge it with concatenate\n",
    "#calculate the total steps (average)\n",
    "def get_average_steps(df):\n",
    "    steps_per_visit = df.groupby('visit_id').size() #group by visit\n",
    "    return steps_per_visit.mean() #get the average\n",
    "\n",
    "# calculate the kpi for each web\n",
    "kpi_part1 = get_average_steps(web_pt1)\n",
    "kpi_part2 = get_average_steps(web_pt2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 1: {kpi_part1:.2f} steps \")\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 2: {kpi_part2:.2f} steps\")\n",
    "print(f\"Diference: {kpi_part2 - kpi_part1:.2f}  steps\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e5eeaae0-5110-48a9-9aeb-5cba0b1f1f74",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "KPI- Time in funnel \n",
    "This KPI is a User Experience and efficiency metric that measures the total duration of a customer's interaction within the digital process during a specific session."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "286f7c3d-26dc-4804-8e76-d60ecaac206d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Web Part 1: 302.77 seconds\n",
      "Web Part 2: 331.20 seconds\n",
      "Diference: 28.43 seconds\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_timefunnel_kpi(df):\n",
    "    times = df.groupby('visit_id')['date_time'].agg(['min', 'max']) #get the min and max by visit\n",
    "    durations = (times['max'] - times['min']).dt.total_seconds() #time by sconf\n",
    "    return durations.mean()\n",
    "# Calculate the KPI\n",
    "time_1 = calculate_timefunnel_kpi(web_pt1)\n",
    "time_2 = calculate_timefunnel_kpi(web_pt2)\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 1: {time_1:.2f} seconds\")\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 2: {time_2:.2f} seconds\")\n",
    "print(f\"Diference: {time_2 - time_1:.2f} seconds\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "85fd76ca-d747-49b5-acf8-6f342c70e78a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "KPI Reached Confirm\n",
    "It represents the Completion Rate of the funnel. It measures the percentage of unique sessions that successfully reached the final \"confirm\" stage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "048cc9f2-2b26-449d-9266-31e2df1765f7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Web Part 1: 52.91% of confirm (39818 of 75256 sesions)\n",
      "Web Part 2: 60.37% of confirm (50008 of 82841 sesions)\n",
      "Diference: 7.46%\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_confirm_rate(df):\n",
    "    reached_confirm = df[df['process_step'] == 'confirm']['visit_id'].nunique() #count the sessions that achieve confirm\n",
    "    total_sessions = df['visit_id'].nunique()\n",
    "    #get the %\n",
    "    rate = (reached_confirm / total_sessions) * 100\n",
    "    return reached_confirm, total_sessions, rate\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the KPI\n",
    "count1, total1, rate1 = calculate_confirm_rate(web_pt1)\n",
    "count2, total2, rate2 = calculate_confirm_rate(web_pt2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 1: {rate1:.2f}% of confirm ({count1} of {total1} sesions)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 2: {rate2:.2f}% of confirm ({count2} of {total2} sesions)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Diference: {rate2 - rate1:.2f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9ba22d1d-6b1e-4b3b-9fbf-2d23ee595ead",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "KPI Has Backward Step / Error Sequence\n",
    "This KPI identifies non linear navigation, which is a proxy for user confusion or technical friction.\n",
    "If a user goes from \"Step 2\" back to \"Step 1\", it suggests they realized they made a mistake, forgot information, or the system failed to validate their input."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "69727bc5-850a-4554-ab7f-65adfc54fb8e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Web Part 1: 23.28% sessions with error (17517 of 75256)\n",
      "Web Part 2: 27.76% sessions with error(22999 of 82841)\n",
      "Diference: 4.49%\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#define the steps by number\n",
    "step_order = {'start': 0, 'step_1': 1, 'step_2': 2, 'step_3': 3, 'confirm': 4}\n",
    "\n",
    "def calculate_backward_rate(df):\n",
    "    df = df.sort_values(['visit_id', 'date_time']) #order\n",
    "    df['step_value'] = df['process_step'].map(step_order) #assign the number to the steps\n",
    "    #calulate the diference \n",
    "    df['is_backward'] = df.groupby('visit_id')['step_value'].diff() < 0\n",
    "    #count the visits that got a return to the previous steps\n",
    "    sessions_with_backward = df[df['is_backward'] == True]['visit_id'].nunique()\n",
    "    total_sessions = df['visit_id'].nunique()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return sessions_with_backward, total_sessions, (sessions_with_backward / total_sessions) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "#calculate the results\n",
    "count1, total1, rate1 = calculate_backward_rate(web_pt1)\n",
    "count2, total2, rate2 = calculate_backward_rate(web_pt2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 1: {rate1:.2f}% sessions with error sequence ({count1} of {total1})\")\n",
    "print(f\"Web Part 2: {rate2:.2f}% sessions with error sequence({count2} of {total2})\")\n",
    "print(f\"Diference: {rate2 - rate1:.2f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
